This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object classification networks and natural images. It also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the correspondence between deep neural networks and human representations, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques to correct discrepancies in the representations could also suggest that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the extension of psychological experiments, which could place it in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
